serves: 40.0
---
- 1.0kg tofu
- 1.3333333333333333kg cauliflower
- 2.0kg gluten free soba noodles
- 0.46666666666666673kg gluten free soy sauce
- 13.333333333333334tbsp rice vinegar
- 20.0tbsp sesame oil
- 1.6666666666666667tsp black pepper
- 6.666666666666667tbsp sugar
- 6.666666666666667tbsp canola oil
- 1.3333333333333333kg green onion
- 20.0tbsp sesame seeds
---
Bring a large pot of water to a boil and cook the soba noodles for 4-5 minutes until tender, stirring occasionally so the noodles don't clump. Drain and rinse well under cold water.
Drain and squeeze the tofu. Cut/tear the tofu and cauliflower to bite size pieces. Mince 0.25 of the green onion, chop the rest to 4cm long pieces. 
Heat a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add the canola oil and heat until shimmering. Saute the tofu and califlower until lightly browned. Add chopped green onions and cook, stirring, for another minute or until fragrant.
Add the soy and sesame mixture and cook for 30 seconds, Add the noodles and toss until the noodles are heated through. Add the remaining minced green onion and sesame seeds.
Serve warm or at room temperature.
